
[1]waver

   WAVER, v.i.

   1. To play or move to and fro; to move one way and the other.

   2. To fluctuate; to be unsettled in opinion; to vacillate; to be
   undetermined; as, to waver in opinion; to waver in faith.

   Let us hold fast the profession of our faith without wavering. Hebrews
   10.

   3. To totter; to reel; to be in danger of falling.

    WAVER, n. A name given to a sapling or young timber tree in England.
